The people of Enugu Akwu Achi in the Oji River Local Government Area of Enugu State have commended the kind gesture by the Manager, Communications, Chevron Nigeria Limited, Mr. Victor Anyaegbudike, who on Thursday, donated food items to over 150 indigent widows in the community. The town union’s President, Mr. Christian Iloma, in a statement on Sunday, extolled the humanitarian attributes of the donor. “The donation is in addition to several other activities he had supported in the town including the Obodo ukwu electricity project, the furnishing of the Enugu Akwu health centre, water project, donations to sick people, and educational grants,” Iloma said. Also, the councillor in charge of Enugu Akwu Ward 2 in the Oji River Local Government Area, Mr Nonso Chijioke, thanked the donor for the kind gesture. He described the donor as an unassuming young man with an undoubted passion for community development, high leadership propensity and altruism, adding that the gesture to the widows showcased his humane disposition. Chijioke urged others to emulate the kind gestures of Anyaegbudike and contribute to societal development to leave an enduring legacy in the sands of time. Reacting, Anyaegbudike said the gesture was to assist the widows and wish them a blissful new year. He affirmed his passion for sustainable development in his community and beyond, saying he always wished for a society where individuals and organisations could partner relevant bodies to sponsor community development.